{
    "info": {
        "_postman_id": "c1f7b0b1-4c6e-4f1d-91a5-8a2a07c1af82",
        "name": "TaskHub API",
        "description": "Postman collection for TaskHub REST API — Authentication & Task Management.\n\nAvailable query parameters for GET /api/tasks:\n- `priority` (string): Filter by priority level. Accepted: low, moderate, high\n- `status` (string): Filter by completion status. Accepted: pending, completed\n- `deadline` (string): Filter tasks with approaching deadline. Accepted: approaching\n- `sort` (string): Sort order. Accepted: newest (default), oldest, priority, deadline\n- `page` (integer): Page number to retrieve. Default: 1\n- `per_page` (integer): Number of tasks per page. Default: 10, max: 100\n\nResponse envelope for GET /api/tasks:\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": [ /* array of task objects with need_attention flag */ ],\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"current_page\": 1,\n    \"last_page\": 5,\n    \"per_page\": 10,\n    \"total\": 47,\n    \"from\": 1,\n    \"to\": 10\n  },\n  \"links\": {\n    \"first\": \"http://...\",\n    \"last\": \"http://...\",\n    \"prev\": null,\n    \"next\": \"http://...&page=2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\ncreated by risyandi.com - 2026",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
